subSubSection.paragraph:
Coloration.
General coloration light greenish (
Fig. 4
). Metazona, tegmina, mandibles, movable spines of fore- and middle tibiae, tarsomeres and apex of male cerci light brownish. Flagellomeres and apical part of ovipositor dark brownish. Immature with little brownish spots on pronotum, on head above the eyes, and legs (
Fig. 5
).
